comments.body:
Would this be better as:

```c++
    assert(!blocksConnected.empty());  // cannot call GetBlocksConnected() twice
    assert(!blocksConnected.back().pindex);
    blocksConnected.pop_back();

    std::vector<PerBlockConnectTrace> result;
    std::swap(result, blocksConnected);
    return result;
```

so that `blocksConnected` is left in a well-defined empty state?

